{{Underline|1069b9}}<div align="center"><font size="6"><span style="text-shadow: 0px 0px 10px #1069b9, 0px 0px  #1069b9">< Entities</span></font></div>{{Underline|1069b9}}
{{Entity Class|Agg=2|Int=3|Dan=5|noname=3|no=N/A|Hab=[[Level 104]], [[Level 4]], [[Level 33]] and [[Level 36]]}}
{{Blurimage|file=Aufpassen.png|caption=Always watching..|hovertext=Aufpassen..}}{{Blurimage|file=Danger Ahead.png|caption=Danger Ahead..|hovertext=Seien Sie vorsichtig im Bereich des Plexus...}}The only entity in '''Level 104''' is '''"The Last NASA Worker"''', usually only displaying its upper face and dark, tangled hair before retreating, appearing as a partially hidden humanoid mass buried behind low barriers or corners. Its eyes can always be seen, reflecting dim light in a lifeless, predatory way, even when it's almost completely dark outside. The thing likes to hide itself in tight passageways and sharp turns, just out of sight enough to make people scared or curious. Wanderers often say that it seems to be standing still and quietly watching before disappearing when it is directly approached.
<br>
'''The Last NASA Worker''', who has a '''2/5 Aggression Rating''', follows people around instead of attacking them right away. It only hunts certain wanderers if in a group, testing people's reactions, learning their patterns of movement, and staying hidden while following its prey for long periods of time. It can handle simple issues thanks to its '''3/5 Intellect Rating'''. It has been seen blocking escape routes, guessing turns, and changing the lighting by hovering near shaky fixtures.
<br>
<br>
Its lethality of attacks earns it a full 5/5 Danger Rating despite its restrained aggression. When it decides to attack, it speeds up quickly, comes out of hiding, and attacks from close range. When someone gets hurt, they usually die within seconds, and survivors are very rare and have reported the anomaly to '''[[M.E.G.|M.E.G]]'''. The thing shows up out of the blue from low buildings or blind spots, preferring to ambush than chase. Its preferred place to hunt and kill are narrow hallways, so it is advised to immediately run upon visual sight. Do not stare, approach, or try to hide there.
{{Underline|1069b9}}<div align="center"><font size="6"><span style="text-shadow: 0px 0px 10px #1069b9, 0px 0px 5px #1069b9, 0px 0px 10px #1069b9">< Addendum</span></font></div>{{Underline|1069b9}}
