Due to the nature of '''Level 104''', '''Colonies & Outposts''' cannot be established. Multiple people from [[M.E.G.|M.E.G]] and [[Backroom Colonists|The Backrooms Colonists]] have entered '''Level 104''', all dead.
{{Underline|1069b9}}<div align="center"><font size="6"><span style="text-shadow: 0px 0px 10px #1069b9, 0px 0px 5px #1069b9, 0px 0px 10px #1069b9">< Entrances & Exits</span></font></div>{{Underline|1069b9}}
{{Underline|1069b9}}<div align="center"><font size="5"><span style="text-shadow: 0px 0px 10px #1069b9, 0px 0px 5px #1069b9, 0px 0px 10px #1069b9">Entrances</span></font></div>{{Underline|1069b9}}
*Wandering through office based levels like [[Level 4]] and walking through a narrow corridor may bring one to '''Level 104'''.

*Interacting with powered CRT monitors that display static in [[Level 140]] will bring one to '''Level 104'''.

*Noclipping while pressed against two narrow walls in dark areas will bring one here.

*Following announcements stating ''"Please remain at your workstation"'' may alter hallway geometry until the environment becomes blue, which will send one to '''Level 104'''.
{{Underline|1069b9}}<div align="center"><font size="5"><span style="text-shadow: 0px 0px 10px #1069b9, 0px 0px 5px #1069b9, 0px 0px 10px #1069b9">Exits</span></font></div>{{Underline|1069b9}}
*Entering rooms labeled ''"Emergency Evacuation"'' sometimes leads to maintenance tunnels that eventually connect to Class 5 and Class Deadzone levels, though these routes are unstable.

*Throwing an object to distract the entity has allowed wanderers to noclip through thin walls, exiting into [[Level 399]] or [[Level 20]].

*In rare cases, finding a red light on the floor and stepping directly onto it will force an effect out of '''Level 104''' to [[Level 81]].

*Successfully losing sight and finding one's exact path for five minutes may return wanderers to safer office, mall and airport levels such as [[Level 33]], [[Level 36]] or [[Level 4]].

